# Ticket Status State Machine

This table is the **single source of truth** for allowed transitions:

| From | Allowed To |
|------|------------|
| Open | In Progress, Cancelled |
| In Progress | Resolved, Cancelled |
| Resolved | Closed |
| Closed | *(none)* |
| Cancelled | *(none)* |

## Enforcement Rules

- **Every status change MUST go through** `src/backend/app/services/ticket_status.py` (`can_transition` / `transition`).
- Expose status changes **only** via `POST /api/tickets/{id}/status`.
- **Never** accept `status` on `PATCH /api/tickets/{id}` or any generic update endpoint.
- **Invalid transitions** must raise `InvalidTransitionError` and return **HTTP 409** with the standard error shape.
- Frontend status buttons must offer **only** transitions valid from the current status.

## Status Values

`Open`, `In Progress`, `Resolved`, `Closed`, `Cancelled` — fixed enums, no free-text status.
